init_text: Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: this power is not enough to defeat the invaders.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: However, these spurts are enough to cause all sorts of things to change-including the abilities of those who possess it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: loss of memory, hallucinations, and strange abilities.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The survivors who possess Mana are sent out into space to be what they call "Watchers" of the Earth.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: their counterattacks are so few and so disorganized, but the humans soon discover that they possess other strengths.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the women are now able to give birth to girls twice as frequently as before, and the men are able to produce much more sperm.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: then launch a last-ditch attempt to destroy the humans on Earth, but this too ends fail as the humans fight back with considerable strength.
